hopobject.body: Lost credit card how long do lamictal withdrawal symptoms last The government shutdown will result in the furlough of all FAA Aviation Safety Inspectors (ASI) each of whom is in place because risks have been identified to exist without them. By performing 750,000 safety inspections each year, ASIs ensure the airlines operate at the highest level of safety, on behalf of the traveling public, at training centers, hangers, airports, and aboard hundreds of revenue flights every day. Every day that is, until now. Congress has decided (thank you very much), that performing those 2,900 daily safety inspections, targeted at already identified air transportation risks with the sole purpose of keeping the traveling public safe, is no longer important. Think about that as you drive to the airport this week.
